text: <@U0548MM6B> actually, there's a Chrome flag to enable WebAPKs
but performance wise, I still see them stutter, lag and not being on the native level.
So i'm just going to come right out and say it
You take a native app running on the device
rewrite it in a scripting language
then put it in the browser
and run it on the system
I think this “web is the new native” is just JS tards trying to find the easiest way to justify shit they’re doing
you just added 1 more layer of abstraction, cost the user more cpu, ram and battery life
which power-wise is still beating smartphones
and we see how that works.
no matter how you look at it it's ridiculous
VM on top of VM on top of VM
how about we stop trying to add more VMs and fix the actual problems
you can defeat any pro JS argument by saying ‘alright show me how to access a USB device'
“well you just write that part in native code"
<@U055GGAHS> they will always say node support is coming
so basically it doesn’t solve anything they just feel like its better because they already know it

web devs have the same issue as other "new-stack" devs, they tend to repeat the same mistakes from "older-stack" devs. There is a reason why we don't have the majority of desktop apps being in the multi-platform Java, because multiple platforms accessibility hurts performance. Same exact thing with React, yes it's nice to write once and run everywhere, but the user won't use your web app again since it's shittily slow
and of course lack of native APIs
it just doesn't work, Apple and Google don't care about having a unified platform so it's impossible to create a unified app
even with native APIs you still can’t cover everything you ever need to do with some helper libraries and javascript just flat sucks for working with bytes
<@U055GGAHS> well, to be fair there are web apis for USB
<@U053LEHJN> as a language dev you should know by now that you can't abstract everything
at the end of the day you need to start looking at what you actually get vs what you want
I can’t imagine trying to do this from javascript
how do you even thread on it
my big problem is adding yet another VM
it goes down in the VM
and fuck everyone shoving JS in everyone’s throat
<@U08GFT5V5> even on mobile it's still just V8
“oh it’s a phone? JS ON IT!"
it's not running on a VM
“oh it’s a PC? JS ON IT!"
“oh it’s a Pi? JS ON IT!"
I'm saying it's not nested or anything
“OH IT'S A GOD DAMN SATELLITE? PUT SOME GOD DAMN JS ON IT!"
I bet SpaceX wrote all their software for the rockets in JS. :trollface: :
I bet the last one blew up because facebook wrote some js for their satellite :stuck_out_tongue:

I dislike either side in this argument. From a business perspective PWAs a awesome cause you can get the audience that doesn't download apps. And believe me that exists. I see web apps as complimentary and actually another way to engage users to download your native app. It eases them into the space and well of course then again out of the bull crap that JS is :troll:
